# Data Directory Structure

## File Organization

| Directory       | Content Description                  | Key Files Example                     |
|-----------------|--------------------------------------|---------------------------------------|
| `01_growth/`    | Body measurements and weight data    | `growth_measures.xlsx`                |
| `02_behavior/`  | Behavioral observations              | `behavior_cross_sucking.xlsx`         |
| `03_environment/` | Climate and THI records            | `environment_thi_records.xlsx`        |
| `04_feeding/`   | Feeding and water intake data        | `feeding_water_intake.xlsx`           |

## Naming Convention
Files follow: `[domain]_[content]_[detail].xlsx`

- **Domain**: 
  - `growth`: Weight gain and Body measurements
  - `behavior`: Animal behavior (Active, Lying, Cross-sucking)
  - `environment`: Climate data
  - `feeding`: Nutrition intake (Water and Feed intake)

- **Content**: 
  - `measures`: Quantitative data
  - `scan`: Time-based observations
  - `events`: Discrete occurrences
